y=3x-5\cos^2(\pi x)
y=3x-5\cos^2(\pi x)
y' = 3 - 2\cdot 5\cdot \pi \cos(\pi x)(-\sin(\pi x)) = 3 + 5\pi(2\sin(\pi x)\cos(\pi x)) =  3 + 5\pi\sin(2\pi x)
y = 3x - 5\cos\Big((\pi x)^2\Big)
\begin{align} y' & = 3 - \left[-5 \sin\Big((\pi x)^2\Big)\right]\cdot \frac{d}{dx}\Big((\pi x)^2 \Big) \\ \\ & = 3 - \left[-5 \sin\Big((\pi x)^2\Big)\right]\cdot \frac{d}{dx}\Big(\pi^2 x^2 \Big)\\ \\ & = 3 + 5  \sin\Big((\pi x)^2\Big)\cdot (2\pi^2 x) \\ \\ & = 3 + 10\pi^2 x\cdot  \sin\Big((\pi x)^2\Big)\end{align}
